207
00:14:29,874 --> 00:14:30,867
Too easy.

208
00:14:30,891 --> 00:14:33,857
Instead, we'll play a game.

209
00:14:33,881 --> 00:14:35,861
Oh, you're gonna love playing shuffleboard

210
00:14:35,885 --> 00:14:36,868
in Arkham, Riddler!

211
00:14:36,892 --> 00:14:38,874
Shh..

212
00:14:38,898 --> 00:14:43,865
The game is 20 questions twenty yes or no's

213
00:14:43,889 --> 00:14:45,010
from which my brilliant mind

214
00:14:45,885 --> 00:14:48,898
will deduce the true identity of The Batman.

215
00:14:55,896 --> 00:14:57,913
'Now, see the lie detector?'

216
00:15:00,917 --> 00:15:03,896
Answer falsely, Batman, and Yinsy here

217
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:07,893
'gets more than just the shock of learning your identity.'

218
00:15:07,917 --> 00:15:09,891
Don't tell him anything, Batman!

219
00:15:09,915 --> 00:15:11,896
Question number one.

220
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:13,931
Do you have blond hair?

221
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:17,927
He has pink hair. He's from the moon.

222
00:15:18,930 --> 00:15:20,916
Blond, yes or no?

223
00:15:20,940 --> 00:15:21,944
Yes.

224
00:15:26,946 --> 00:15:29,909
'Consider that a sample.'

225
00:15:29,933 --> 00:15:32,947
With every false answer, the voltage spikes.

226
00:15:33,947 --> 00:15:36,927
Question two, Bat-brunet.

227
00:15:36,951 --> 00:15:39,938
Were you born here in Gotham City?

228
00:15:39,962 --> 00:15:43,964
- 'Yes.' - 'That's the spirit.'

229
00:15:46,964 --> 00:15:48,934
The riddles ended.

230
00:15:48,958 --> 00:15:49,944
Yin vanished in thin air

231
00:15:49,968 --> 00:15:52,930
